 themes as women artists, African American representation and expression, regional and itinerant artists, Native Americans and the frontier, popular culture and vernacular imagery, institutional history, and more. With its hundreds of explanatory headnotes providing essential context and guidance to readers, this book reveals the documentary riches of American art and its many intersecting histories in unprecedented breadth, depth, and detail.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aArt, AmericanxSources. 7aART / American / General.2bisacsh  a18th century american art history.  a19th century american art history.  aafrican american art.  aamerican art.  aart.  aartists.  abenjamin west.  achester harding.  acotton mather.  ahistorical.  ainstitutional history.  ajohn adams.  ajohn durand.  ajohn singleton copley.  ajohn smibert.  ajohn valentine haidt.  anative american artists.  apainters.  apaintings.  apeter pelham.  apopular culture.  apuritanism.  aquakers.  aregional artists.  asculptors.  astylistic manifestos.  atheory of painting.  athomas smith.  avernacular imagery.  avisual art.  awomen artists.  aworks of art.1 aBurns, Sarah, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aDavis, John, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013z97831106904220 cprintz978052025756640uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/9780520943827?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520943827423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520943827/original  a978-3-11-069042-2  University of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-UCY